      "acceptanceCriteria": "SQA procedures documented; version control and regression testing in place for CFD solver.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022R2) is a commercially validated code with documented SQA processes. Internal version control and regression test suite confirm compliance with MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems solved to confirm solver accuracy for relevant flow regimes.",
      "rationale": "Standard benchmark cases including lid-driven cavity and backward-facing step were solved with results matching published reference solutions within 1% for velocity profiles, confirming numerical code correctness."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study demonstrating GCI < 5% for hemolysis index QoI across at least three mesh refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "A two-level mesh refinement study was performed (coarse and medium grids only). The grid convergence index for the hemolysis index QoI was estimated at approximately 9.3%, exceeding the 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation was not completed due to computational resource constraints. The team judged this acceptable given agreement with experimental data, but the formal GCI criterion is not satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Experimental operating conditions were taken from published FDA pump dataset. However, fluid temperature during experiments was not recorded, introducing uncertainty in blood viscosity of approximately ±8%. Boundary condition matching is partial; inlet velocity profile was assumed uniform rather than measured."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of predicted vs. measured hemolysis index with normalized error < 15% across all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute percentage error was 11.4%, within the 15% acceptance threshold. Systematic underprediction at high-speed conditions was noted but deemed within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to clinical hemolysis endpoints; relative hemolysis index RH is the primary decision metric.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the clinical decision criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate device). Secondary QoIs including shear stress exposure time and scalar stress distributions support mechanistic interpretation and are clinically relevant."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on geometry and flow conditions sufficiently similar to COU device and operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which shares impeller design features with the COU device. Operating conditions span the clinical flow-speed envelope. Geometric fidelity and flow similarity are judged adequate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error beyond code verification is not required at Model Risk Level 2 for Class II devices. Factor scoped out per MRL 2 assessment matrix."
    },
    {
